{
  "texts": [
    "To compare continuous-valued abundances, we defined the abundance of a plasmid in a metagenome as the sum of coverage values across all sequence positions divided by sequence length, and we defined the abundance of a taxon as Bracken's estimate of the number of reads originating from the taxon.",
    "If a plasmid had a detection of <95%, then we set its abundance to zero.",
    "If a taxon had <1,000 reads, then we set its abundance to zero.",
    "We ignored plasmids and taxa that had non-zero abundances in fewer than five metagenomes.",
    "For every pair of plasmid and taxon, we estimated the Pearson correlation between their abundance levels across metagenomes using FastSpar 89 v1.0.0 (https:// github.com/scwatts/fastspar), which is an improved implementation of the SparCC 90."
  ]
}